						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is damaged. It registers the sale of half a <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land tax-free for twenty <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> by the assembly of Parāntaka-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Muḍiyūr-nāḍu to a certain Paṭṭan Pūvan (?) whom they helped to settle in their village and also gave him the surname Parāntaka-Pēraiyaṉ after the name of the village. At the bottom of the record is a fragment of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of king Rājēndradēva.</p>						

						</summary>
